                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240407-88-victim816 t18240407-88-viclabel490"></join>, and live at <rs id="t18240407-88-viclabel491" type="occupation">Shadwell</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240407-88-victim816 t18240407-88-viclabel491"></join>. On the 25th of March, the prisoner came and asked to see some 1 s. 6 d. knives, which I shewed him - he asked to see some more; he was above an hour in the shop, and while I was reaching him some I saw him put one into his hat, and another into his pocket; he offered 10 d. for one, which I refused. He went out; I followed and took him - he pulled the knife out, and said,</p>

               <p>"Here d - n you, here is the knife; I did it in a lark." I thought he was tipsy.</p>
